thread.title: Bay Area’s food-delivery boom and its ethical dilemma

author: Jonathan Kauffman
title: Bay Area’s food-delivery boom and its ethical dilemma
text:
Cynthia Marciano has been driving for DoorDash since October 2014, and up until July, she loved the work. The 30-year-old had been in customer service — sandwich shops, pool halls — for most of her career, but DoorDash was different: The on-demand delivery service has let her choose her lunch and dinner shifts and set her own income goals, usually $600 a week.
